## Updating the ~/.ssh/config profile will make the ssh login simpler. E.g., ssh gauravsinghal@<ip address> to ssh gs 
Host gs
    HostName <ip address>
    User <ssh username>            ##e.g., gauravsinghal
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/gs-aws-key.pem            ## if .pem key is generated on the AWS server, else deactivate the command
    IdentitiesOnly yes


